social_posts.post_text: 12/12/22 looks who’s 2! Happy birthday to my baby girl, Valor. Being her mom has been a tremendous blessing. She’s super smart, curious, and her personality fills any room. It has been a joy to watch her grow and learn. I’ve never witnessed a little human developing this close up before. It’s like one day she woke up counting and speaking full sentences. Time is wild and God is kind 💜 happy birthday Valor Girl, My World 🥳

TURN UP TWO! We celebrated our girl with a kiddie turn up like only she would have it. Valor and her mini crew had a blast @readysetfunatl they would barely sit down to eat. She’s a prissy girl who loves to play hard so I knew this venue would be perfect. Their awesome team helped us turn their girly spa room into a party space. Let’s get into the details shall we? Balloons, backdrop and centerpiece by @lencreates who always comes through for my girl.  She executed the concept from @gracegigglesandglue who provided the hip hop girls theme along with the personalized gift bags, cups, and cupcake toppers. Owner @kellibradford7 gave us the party blueprint and this will now be a new theme on her site. The cupcakes were a hit thanks to @teetee.eats just the right amount of sweetness for the little ones. The adults tore the red velvet up! I can’t thank these black female entrepreneurs enough for executing our vision to perfection. Valor had the time of her life. Thanks to our village for showing up strong 🥳💜
UNCF Mayor’s Masked Ball 2022 #uncfmayorsballatl22

The category is: Black Barbie! The glam squad was down to cause a little commotion. Let’s hear it for the girls!!!

#uncfmayorsballatl22
The @11alive Morning News Team White Elephant Christmas Party! Love this team. Glad we took time to celebrate the early morning sacrifice and all the hard work it takes to do what we do 🙌🏾

Happy New Yearrrr! Mine started today because 2023 came in and sat me all the way down disrespectfully 😩 started the year with laryngitis. Couldn’t fully speak for 4 days 😶 How does that work when you talk for a living 😂 after vocal rest and all the concoctions you can concoct…I’m glad to be back! #AnchorBaeInTheA

My girl came to visit me at work for the first time today. My co-workers were 🤏🏾this close to locking me out the building if I didn’t bring her in soon 😂 they ate her right on up and she had them wrapped around her finger in seconds with her personality. She walked around like she owned the place saying “mommy go to work. Mommy on tv.” The work aunties are ready to bring her on full time 🤣
We got the money shot 💰📸
Hey, I’m just the messenger! Netflix said it’s a new day and everybody gotta pay! The crackdown on password sharing is expected to happen sometime in the first quarter of this year. #AnchorBaeInTheA

I made @jimmykimmellive last night along with 100 other news anchors who were shocked it was February 1st 😂🤯 hilarious because this was an ad lib…not in the teleprompter. But for real CAN YOU BELIEVE IT’S FEBRUARY 🤣 Kimmel does these mash ups often. Shout out to whoever finds the clips. They’re hilarious!
Let’s hear a little commotion for the suit @chesleymcneil Popped out looking dapper on us this morning and we were not ready. Que dog swag was on 💯 TALK SLOW! @cheryl.preheim @therealcrashclark

Hello 38 🎉 I’ve made it to see 222 again and I’m just thankful to be here with the people I love, doing what I love. Here’s to another year of closing the gap between who I am now and the woman God showed me I have the potential to be ✨my birthday prayer this morning: “God bless me with fewer things that hold more value. I don’t want it all, I want the weight.”

Word to the ladies showing up in the name of culture and convenience in all of your magical knotless braided glory 🙌🏾 wishing you all seamless mornings with your get ready time cut in half. Productive workouts without your edges laughing in the face of edge control. Smiling as you respond to those who feel they control the definition of professional and what is or isn’t. Sistas y’all alright?

Decided yesterday morning to get braids. Babyyyy @estherafrican_braids DID THAT!! Full and super neat. Thanks ladies!

Got to interview the legendary ladies of Xscape today all about their new Bravo reality show, “The Queens of R&B” They were real and as down to earth as they come. Catch the interview tomorrow morning on @11alive Morning News as we talk about their desire to move on from all the drama unfolding in their group. Thanks @neimerdreamer for letting me be a part of your thriving Culture Content!

I sat down with the ladies of Xscape to talk about their new show SWV & Xscape: The Queens of R&B. We see the group and family drama has only escalated each week. Despite that, I asked if the ladies were showing women an example of reconciling broken relationships…everyone wasn’t so sure 😂 @kandi @majorgirl @therealtamikascott

With all the drama surrounding @therealtamikascott and her sister I loved how @majorgirl and @kandi supported her in this moment. They took time to push her into her own solo greatness when I asked the ladies if we can expect new music soon! Push your friends into the greatness you know they’re sleeping on 🙌🏾

God, we need you. Don’t let us miss you in the midst of our heartbreak as we mourn the loss of our sister and friend, Mel. Many of us can’t fathom the idea of burying a friend at this stage of our lives. We are all simply stomped by this. I chose these photos of Mel to depict her character…the book a flight friend who wouldn’t miss celebrating her loved ones. Mel always found time to check in and be present...a lesson I’ll take from this loss. You were more than my line sister, but a true friend. I will miss you dearly, Mel 
🕊️🤍 🕊️

No school uniform today, instead Valor and her classmates got to wear their favorite Spring outfit for their Easter Egg Hunt. She knew the vibes was different because my girl was feeling herself heavy 😂 I’m too outdone with my little human and this big personality! Valor girl, my world 🥰 she’s such a bright light!

Play ball!! It’s opening day for our @braves we took our morning show on the road live from inside Truist Park, on the field, before the sun came out. So many new things in store this year enhancing the fan experience! Have a great season guys and let’s do it “For the A” shoutout to our amazing team for a flawless live broadcast 🙌🏾❤️
Pick a side, ain’t no switching up 🤍🖤 #AnchorBaeInTheA 📸 @_kev908

My sister-friend turned 40 and it was an honor to celebrate such a beautiful person! Noey, I love and cherish our friendship. I’ve learned so much from you personally and professionally…it’s truly invaluable. The Joan Clayton to my Toni Childs you’re just getting better and more fine with time 🎉💜 414 😂 @_itsnoey

Yesterday I decided to randomly take my braids down with NO hair appointment scheduled. I took my Instagram story friends on my journey of bad decisions. As a news anchor my hair has to be on point but I was up the creek without a paddle 😅 Miraculously, by showtime I was TV ready but not without the jokes being on me 😂 notice the time stamps. They were on my head from 430-7am 🤣  Please catch that shade from @rarione.maniece 😂😂 Yesterday’s hair drama is at the end of the reel! Thanks to everyone who sent suggestions and offered to help!

My morning anchor routine in 45 seconds! My alarm goes off at 2:45am. I’m on air by 4:30am. Back in my sweats by 7:15am. True to this, not new to this. To do this, you gotta love this. I was born for this. 💫 #AnchorBaeInTheA

I’m honored to grace the cover of @simplybuckhead along with @chesleymcneil for the May edition that’s all about philanthropy! The cover shoot was in partnership with @11alive and our friends at @acfb Chesley and I have enjoyed hosting their annual Hunger Walk for the last two years raising money to feed local families…along with our many individual philanthropic contributions and through our fraternity and sorority. So while I love beauty and fashion to have my first magazine cover in Atlanta to focus on giving back speaks to my true purpose and passion. Thank you for the opportunity 🙏🏾

Hair: @bflyyexperience 
Makeup: @cheriebeauty_

2 Emmy nominations! Last year I told myself for the first time I’d enter my work in the anchor category next time. I was so nervous and second guessed myself every step of the way…as I thought “why hadn’t you done this before. Everyone else knows what they’re doing and how to put their work together so no way you’ll get nominated.” I kept pulling my work and editing it together through the imposter syndrome. I prayed and submitted on the final day. Here we are nominated in the anchor category. Additionally I’m proud of our entire morning team for our newscast nomination. We won this category last year and we’ve only grown since then. Looking forward to celebrating with all the amazing @southeastemmy nominees!! So glad I changed the conversation I was having with myself, about myself!! You deserve to be there Eish!!

Shot my first image campaign with our super talented @11alive marketing team today…think of it as a get to know me commercial. @courtneycarolineg asked me a few questions about showing up on your tv screens as my authentic self…the one who says weed instead of pot and will drop a Drake reference, or talk about a bad natural hair/weave day, and relates to life in Zone 1.  Atlanta, thank you for embracing ME…not a news anchor. Excited to see how this turns out. Appreciate you @courtneycarolineg for making me feel comfortable on the other side answering the questions this time. And @dream_lensphotography thanks for welcoming our team into your beautiful studio @dls.atl whew chile @jdelormua you put a fierce beat on this face! And if I got a haircut you know @dereqc did it! This team KILLED! #AnchorBaeInTheA
I don’t ever want to miss a word, constructive feedback, or a gem dropped on me because my aura says I’m not open to receive. Gentle reminder…perception does matter 🫶🏾 #AnchorBaeInTheA

Well look who got the weekend started on a Thursday night taking in the best new view in the city @nobuatlanta unveiled their rooftop, pool and villas! @parfumsdemarly brought the French luxury vibe and top tier scents. Thanks to my girl @justtlo for getting me out on a school night and introducing me to some other great women! Sooo is this blue my new color?! #AnchorBaeInTheA

Hey guys please keep Valor and I in your prayers. I put her on a skirt today after she asked everyday this week…plus let her wear a Minnie Mouse purse with lipgloss and money in it…and a bang…so all of a sudden her hips just broke and won’t go back in. We’re praying for a speedy recovery 🙏🏾😂😩
Thankful for the gift of the girl who allows me to celebrate this day. Happy Mother’s Day 💜

Blue 🔷 a spring time love story! How I’m looking at myself when I realized most of my recent late night purchases were the same color 😂#AnchorBaeInTheA

📸 @_kev908

Valor’s first trip to @princesshairpizzazz I tried a luxury kid hair salon hoping she’d be inspired seeing other little girls getting their hair done in a pretty environment. It worked!! Sorta 🥴 the hardest part at home (getting her to lay back on the countertop) was the easiest part at the salon. She didn’t mind the wash bowl. So that was a win! She was coming out of an Afro puff so detangling was a little rough. So we could see she wasn’t going to sit long enough to get all that hair in single twists. But I’m super satisfied with the ponytails. They held up great with a bonnet! And this will be easy for me to manage. Thank you Jasmine and the Cumberland team for your kindness and patience 💜💗

Black excellence, opulence, decadence 💫 beautiful time with beautiful people at today’s Black Media Mixer…bringing journalists from all the Atlanta stations together. Shout out to the hosts for organizing a great occasion. It was needed and appreciated.

Join me for an informative coffee date weekdays on @11alive 430am-7am. And if you’re already part of the morning news fam thanks for starting your day with us 🫶🏾

Thank you to my producer @her_name_is_q for her continued commitment to bring these stories to life 🙌🏾

Look who made her on air debut! She loves “mommy’s work on tv” so I brought her in today since school was closed. Love how my co-workers love her and how she just goes to everyone with ease. A junior social butterfly. She had a blast!

He’s top 2, under 2 and he’s not number 2! I got to meet this viral soccer sensation and tell the story of his Irene’s noticing and nurturing his undeniable talent. Shout out to the Uchendu family for this fun and inspiring piece. See you at the FIFA World Cup in 2038 Starboyy ⚽️
Refilling my cup in Napa ✨

People ask how I survive the 2:45am alarm clock…CAR NAPS!! But sometimes I go in too deep 😂 today was one of those days. My producers usually call me but they left me fa dead on the back row of the parking lot under a shade tree! But I made it in time for the midday news 😅

Valor’s first day of PreK 3 📚 ✏️ I was nervous about her skipping a class but her hunger for knowledge is undeniable. Never hold a scholarly queen back. Let’s go have a great year V!! Ivy League up next 😂
🍫 goodness ☺️

The @11alive morning news team back to school drive is in full swing and we need your help! This year your donations will benefit students at Brookview Elementary and Woodland Middle School in Fulton County. We chose these schools because of the financial challenges their families are facing along with many of the students coming from an unstable home life. We’ve made it easy for you…you can shop and donate from your phone. Follow the link in my bio to see the schools Amazon wish list ✏️ 👕 📓 🖍 This is a cause I relate to and that’s very special to me so I’m thankful to our team for getting behind my passion project.  More than 300 items have been purchased so far…THANK YOU!

The glam squad came through and got violent 😩 @nimzykabibi on the beat and @bflyyexperience on the hair. Ladies, you outdid yourselves 🙌🏾 straight out the iPhone camera roll. *Chefs kiss*  #AnchorBaeInTheA

Because the south got somethin’ to say you can’t celebrate 50 years of hip hop without Atlanta. The A is celebrating with spirit week and today is ATL dance day and this dress is giving “Shoulder Lean” word to @1youngdro and @tip for this certified college party banger I enjoyed all the way at Michigan State. Songs like this had all of us wanting to move to Atlanta soon as we graduated…and we DID 😂 “I can shoulder lean, ion know how to dance though” #AtlantaSpiritWeek #AnchorBaeInTheA

Windy and rainy today! Appropriate time for this throwback video I just found of me trying to get @chesleymcneil to do a wig forecast 😂 I have got to stop playing on these peoples airwaves 😩 if you ever produce a show I’m anchoring don’t bother writing a weather toss for me 😆 sometimes it’s just too early to be so serious! #AnchorBaeInTheA

WE’RE ALL IN THIS TOGETHER! ❤️ ✏️ Thanks to all of your generous donations, we were able to supply Brookview Elementary with hundreds of essential school supplies. We are so grateful for your help making a positive impact in our community. #11Alive #B2S #backtoschool #fultoncountyschools #brookviewelementary #community #givingback #schooldrive #makeadifference

The way God has ordered my steps in my career I have no choice but to give him glory by using this platform to serve the community he placed me in. Last year when I pitched the @11alive back to school drive I got immediate support from my team. This year I wanted to elevate the vision. It didn’t come in the form of how much our viewers donated…it was WHO was on the receiving end. The awesome students at @brookviewelementary make it into that school building despite some tough situations at home. 100% of them receive free or reduced price lunch and 70% are transient students…meaning their housing situation might be unstable. To see how grateful they were getting your donations of not  just “school supplies” but laundry detergent and school uniforms…my heart could have exploded! This video wraps up another successful year and a community initiative that will continue to get greater. Thank you Pandas 🐼 and our amazing partners @fultoncoschools and thanks to the @11alive team for believing in the vision 🫶🏾we are GREAT ON PURPOSE!!

A foot soldier and a man of the movement. Honored to sit down with Ambassador Andrew Young today to talk about the 60th anniversary of the March on Washington. At 91 years old he recalls the 1963 march so clearly and the steps they took months in advance to make it what’s still considered the most impactful racial justice gathering to date. Ambassador Young is a phenomenal storyteller. I hope I do his words justice. Story coming soon to @11alive
Light up the night ✨

Today, August 28th, 2023 we celebrate the 60th anniversary of the March on Washington. It was the birthplace of one of the most iconic speeches to date, Dr. Martin Luther King Jr’s “I Have a Dream” speech. I had the honor of sitting down with Ambassador Andrew Young who was Dr. King’s assistant at the time. I held on to every word as he recounted the Birmingham bombings that caused them to march in Alabama…leading them to take the march all the way to D.C. Thank you Mr. Young for who you are to the nation and Atlanta. Thank you to photojournalist Stephen Boissy for putting this together so beautifully.

It’s our job to bring you stories that impact your community and some of them are heartbreaking. But in the midst of reporting hard news we find bright spots on dark days. Here’s a look back on a great year with my @11alive morning news team edited by @cheryl.preheim

My final story of 2023 came with a powerful message. When you think life takes you down, all it takes is one encounter to lift you back up. Thank you @iamdeannadixon and @whoistedrien for sharing your story of how one Uber ride changed your lives and led to this lifelong friendship!
Her friendship is a gem that’s rare and true! Happy 40th birthday @prettyyoungtae we love and celebrate you 🩷💜💛🧡❤️

The #FourTae grand finale black out while the birthday girl pop out 🙌🏾 20 years of friendship. The iron has been sharpened. Back to reality we go with full hearts. Love you ladies and we missed the rest of the crew!
